event_text: Policy announcement: no one sent offshore will ever be settled in Australia, everyone who comes by boat will be sent offshore. Regional Resettlement Arrangement signed with PNG
Australia signs agreement with Nauru for detention
Memorandum of Understanding with Nauru signed
New MOU supporting the RRA, supersedes previous MOU
First transfer of minors to Nauru RPC
The Liberal National Coalition beats the Australian Labour Party and Tony Abbott becomes Prime Minister. Part of his campaign focused on hardline amendments to Australia's refugee policies
First group of Nauru refugees settled in community
Sayed Ibrahim Hussein dies in Nauru
Deal to send refugees to Cambodia from Nauru
Nauru government directs all unaccompanied minors to be moved from RPCs to acommodation in community
Immigration minister agrees babies born to asylum seekers in Aus on or before 4 December 2014 and their families can have protection claims assessed under Australian system
First two refugees moved to East Lorengau Refugee Transit Centre
Open centre arrangements introduced in Nauru
Nauru becomes open centre (started happening in Feb)
M68 handed down - detention of asylum seekers at Naur RPC authorised under Australian law / LET THEM STAY campaign begins
Supreme Court PNG says detention illegal
Apology to Save The Children workers
First group of refugees leaves Manus for US
Manus centre forcibly closed (NOT SURE OF EXACT DATE)
Rajeev Rajendran dies by suicide in Manus
Last time someone was transferred back to offshore
Last person returned to offshore (according to Estimates)
Last three or four children leave Nauru
People in Australia can now apply to be resettled in the US
